Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pop the potatoes and pepper onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the potatoes are golden and peppers are soft and slightly charred, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @medium tomatoes{2} and chop into 2cm chunks. Pick the @mint{1%sprig}(leaves picked and roughly chopped, stalks discarded) and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Zest and halve the @lemon{½}(zested and halved).

Drain the @halloumi{250%g}, then cut into slices (3 per person). Place them into a small #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Add the lemon zest and @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing to a large bowl and squeeze in the lemon juice. Season with @salt{}, @ground black pepper{} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have any).

Stir to combine, then reserve a few tbsps of dressing for serving in a small bowl. Add the tomatoes and mint to the remaining dressing in the large bowl, then set aside.

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Discard the water from the bowl and wipe it dry, then add the @peri peri seasoning{½%tsp} to it (use less if you don't like heat). Add the halloumi to the seasoning and toss to coat, then set aside.

When 5 mins of roasting time remain, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the spiced halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side, then remove from the heat.

Drizzle the fried halloumi with the @honey{15%ml} and turn to glaze it all over.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for ~{1%minute}.

When the peppers and potatoes are cooked, add them to the large bowl of dressing and toss together with the tomatoes and mint. Spoon your roasted veg salad into #bowls{}, then top with the glazed halloumi slices.

Serve the @wild rocket{40%g} alongside drizzled with the reserved dressing. Enjoy!